OL,7,F"But my father, he did get comfort out
OL,8,Fof it. He saw her and, by all
OL,9,Faccounts, he told me that she ` again,
OL,10,Fthis is typical of the sort of person
OL,11,Fthat my mother was ` that she
OL,12,Fapologised when she was lying on the
OL,13,Fstretcher, moments from death.
OL,15,F"She apologised to my father for being
OL,16,Fcaught up in this incident. She just
OL,17,Ffelt sorry. She apologised that she
OL,18,Fwas even there. She apologised to my
OL,19,Ffather, and God only knows what he
OL,20,Fthought of that."
